README.md

# Buzzmaniam

Buzzmaniam is a read-only, zero-trust analysis system that inspects
Android application artifacts and wireless broadcasts (BLE)
to detect silent components, identity inconsistencies,
and spoofing indicators.

No intrusion. No control. No private data.

## Run
bash run.sh


---

requirements.txt

python>=3.9


---

run.sh

#!/bin/bash
echo "[1] Android artifact scan"
python3 android/artifact_scan.py

echo "[2] Signal log"
python3 signals/signal_log.py

echo "[3] Detect anomalies"
python3 signals/detect_anomaly.py

echo "[4] Regroup + correlate"
python3 core/regroup.py

echo "[5] Policy decision"
python3 core/policy_gate.py


---

android/artifact_scan.py

import zipfile, json

apk = "app-debug.apk"
with zipfile.ZipFile(apk) as z:
    files = z.namelist()

artifact = {
    "dex_count": len([f for f in files if f.endswith(".dex")]),
    "native_libs": [f for f in files if f.startswith("lib/")],
    "has_native": any(f.startswith("lib/") for f in files)
}

print(json.dumps(artifact, indent=2))


---

signals/signal_log.py

import time, json

signals = [
    {"mac": "AA:BB:01", "type": "ESP32"},
    {"mac": "AA:BB:01", "type": "ESP32"},
    {"mac": "AA:BB:02", "type": "LILYGO"}
]

log = {
    "when": time.strftime("%F %T"),
    "what": "BLE_BROADCAST",
    "devices": signals
}

print(json.dumps(log, indent=2))


---

signals/detect_anomaly.py

from collections import Counter
import json

signals = [
    {"mac": "AA:BB:01"},
    {"mac": "AA:BB:01"},
    {"mac": "AA:BB:02"}
]

macs = [s["mac"] for s in signals]
counts = Counter(macs)

anomalies = {
    "duplicate_identifiers": [m for m, c in counts.items() if c > 1]
}

print(json.dumps(anomalies, indent=2))


---

core/regroup.py

import json

artifact = {"has_native": True}
anomalies = {"duplicate_identifiers": ["AA:BB:01"]}

risk = []

if artifact["has_native"]:
    risk.append("Native code present")

if anomalies["duplicate_identifiers"]:
    risk.append("Duplicate BLE identifiers")

decision = "FLAG" if risk else "PASS"

report = {
    "artifact": artifact,
    "anomalies": anomalies,
    "regrouped_findings": risk,
    "decision": decision
}

print(json.dumps(report, indent=2))


---

core/policy_gate.py

decision = "FLAG"
print("STATUS: FLAG — REVIEW REQUIRED" if decision == "FLAG" else "STATUS: PASS")


---

docs/ethics.md

Buzzmaniam operates in read-only mode.

• No device control
• No authentication
• No data extraction
• No identity tracking
• No intrusion

This project demonstrates defensive cybersecurity analysis only.


